FT  17 DEC 94 / Credit Suisse proceedings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN MASON, Law Courts Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Swiss authorities have begun extradition proceedings against an Italian
financier based in London in connection with an alleged Dollars 70m fraud
against Credit Suisse bank. Mr Sergio Cuoghi, the head of the Ehrofin
financial group of Geneva, faces a charge of obtaining Dollars 70m by
deception from Credit Suisse between January 1 1992 and November 18 this
year.
As part of an investigation being carried out by the Swiss authorities, a
former assistant manager with Fides, an investment trust company wholly
owned by Credit Suisse, is currently being held in prison in Geneva. At an
interim hearing at London's Bow St magistrates court yesterday, Mr Cuoghi's
case was adjourned to January 9 next year. Mr Cuoghi, of Montpelier Square,
London, has been remanded on bail until then.
