<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 94 / World News in Brief: Accelerator wins go-ahead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
European states have given the go-ahead for a Dollars 2bn (Pounds 1.3bn)
particle accelerator. The accelerator will fire proton beams around a 27km
tunnel and smash them together to recreate conditions one millionth of a
millionth of a second after the creation of the universe.
