FT  17 DEC 94 / MoD confirms 9,400 redundancies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A total of 9,400 servicemen are to be made redundant as part of the Front
Line First initiative, originally announced in July, the Minstry of Defence
confirmed, yesterday.
Some 1,500 Royal Navy personnel, 7,500 Royal Air Force and some 400 in the
Army will lose their jobs.
The Treasury announced that it is seeking up to 23 volunteers for redundancy
among senior staff, following endorsement of radical internal restructuring
plans by Mr Kenneth Clarke, the chancellor.
The aim is to reduce the number of senior management posts from 100 to 75.
