<TEXT>
The Treasury yesterday announced that it is seeking up to 23 volunteers for
redundancy among senior staff, following endorsement of radical internal
restructuring plans by Mr Kenneth Clarke, the chancellor.
The department wants up to eight volunteers among its grade 3 staff, who are
just below the Treasury's directors in the hierarchy, and up to 15 at grades
4 to 5 - these traditionally count among the cream of Whitehall's mandarins.
The aim is to reduce the number of senior management posts from 100 to 75.
